<!-- V -->
    <div class="section">
      <div class="header">
        <!-- <div class="number-wrapper">1</div> -->
        <h3>I keep getting told to "Just feel the music." And that's not helpful</h3>
        <h4>What to do with the "Just feel the music" advice</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="text">
        <div class="p-header">I heard this before</div>
        <p>You're going to get this answer a lot when you ask how to do freestyle-related things. It's a surprisingly useless answer for how often it comes up, as those who already know what feeling the music means won't need to be told to "Just feel the music," and "Just feel the music" doesn't mean anything to the people who need to be given that answer.</p>

        <div class="p-header">What "Just feel the music" usually means</div>
        <p>--is to imagine the music as movement and to replicate that movement with your being. What's really disappointing however, is that knowing what "Just feel the music" means won't actually help you "Just feel the music."</p>

        <p>But what will help, is to ask anyone who tells you to "Just feel the music" to show you what "Just feel the music" means to them. Then be sure to watch with your eyes and ears, as anyone who gives you that answer will perform in a way where their movements feel like an extension of the music.</p>

        <p>Exposure to different interpretations of "Just feel the music" will eventually get it to click. And once it clicks, your performance of "Just feel the music" might not immediately feel like it meets the standards of someone else's "Just feel the music." And it never will. Even as you improve, your "Just feel the music" will always be unique.</p>

        <p>That's just a constant in freestyle and a reason it's a distinct artform that's difficult to understand and rejected by nearly everyone. As an added bonus, once you understand how to "Just feel the music," you'll likely have found your preferred difficulty, you'll be performing during the gaps between notes, you will know how to "Just do whatever" with your arms, and you won't need this guide anymore.</p>

        <p>By the way, "Just feel the music" doesn't work when you can't really hear the music, Eastridge Mall Round 1.</p>
      </div>

